ce:section.ce:para:
The pyrolysis kinetics of spirulina was studied by thermogravimetric analysis (TG) in a TGA-50 Shimadzu equipment, using sample mass around 10 mg, from 25 °C to 800 °C at four heating rates (5, 10, 15, and 20 °C/min) under a nitrogen atmosphere (50 mL/min). By treating TG curves through isoconversional approaches, it was possible to calculate the kinetic triplet, which is composed of activation energy (E

                           a
                        ), pre-exponential factor (A), and kinetic function f(a) – reaction mechanism parameters. The predictions used the Kissinger-Akahira-Sunose (KAS) and Friedman (FR) methods [31,32].
